Bayelsa State Police Command said yesterday that its operatives have arrested a notorious armed robbery suspect on the wanted list. A statement by the command’s spokesman Asinim Butswat said operatives of its Anti-kidnapping Unit effected the arrest of the suspect, one Keme Azorobor, 27. Butswat said Azorobor, a native of Bomadi Local Government Area, Delta State, but residing in Yenagoa, was arrested during a clearance operation on Otiotio Road, Yenagoa on July 24, 2022, at about 11.45pm.   Appeal Court seeks support over post- 2023 elections…     UPDATED: Buhari seeks Justice Ariwoola’s confirmation…     Interstate transporters begin 25 percent fare increase Aug…   He said the suspect was searched and a locally-made pistol loaded with one live cartridge was recovered from him. Butswat said the suspect had confessed to the level of his involvements in various armed robbery cases being investigated against him and his cohorts, now at large. The police spokesman said investigation was ongoing to arrest his gang members and bring them to book.